-- U.S. Mutual Funds Gather $6.12 Billion in Week on Bond Deposits
-- B y   C h a r l e s   S t e i n
-- 2012-09-19T20:14:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-19/u-s-mutual-funds-gather-6-12-billion-in-week-on-bond-deposits.html
U.S. mutual funds attracted $6.12
billion last week as investors put money into bond funds.  Fixed-income funds gathered $8.11 billion from investors in
the week ended Sept. 12, the Washington-based  Investment Company
Institute  said today in an e-mailed statement. Domestic stock
funds had withdrawals of $2.75 billion, and investors removed
$548 million from international equity funds.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Charles Stein in Boston at 
